SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1468-0262.2008.00839.x
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - We study a Monte Carlo algorithm for computing marginal and stationary densities of stochastic models with the Markov property, establishing global asymptotic normality and OP(n?1/2) convergence. Asymptotic normality is used to derive error bounds in terms of the distribution of the norm deviation.
ER  - 

